                                <p>The Wyrd of Stromgard is an expansion for Dungeon World (created by roleplaying wizards Sage LaTorra and Adam Koebel)- it's a sleek, modern ruleset that lets the collaborative narrative of roleplaying lead the way while the mechanics cleverly quantify contest points in an easy to read and easy to learn format.</p>
                                <p>The rules place priority on story telling, while providing a fun and interesting combat system that doesn't bog itself down being unecessarily verbose or complicated.  It's easy to pick up, easy to get good at, and robust enough to handly really complex, nuanced situations in very common sense ways.</p>
                                <p>One of the things Dungeon World mandates is to "draw maps, but leave blanks" and The Wyrd of Stromgard offers the perfect balance of structure and customizabilty to make the GM's job a little easier and simultaneously provide a fantastic, dynamic setting that play groups can alter and customize any way they please.</p>
                                <p>Getting acquainted with Dungeon World is super easy! Just check out <a href="http://www.dungeon-world.com/">Dungeon World's</a> website for all the info you could possibly need.  Even better, Wyrd of Stromgard player classes can play side by side with vanilla Dungeon World characters seamlessly.</p>
