                                <h2>Literary Roots</h2>
                                <p>The Wyrd of Stromgard takes inspiration from many sources.  You can check out some of our favorite materials below as well as links to free online libraries where you can read them:</p>
                                <div class="realms">
                                    <p>
                                        <strong><a src="https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Poetic_Edda">Poetic Edda</a></strong> - The oldest collection of Norse myths.  Written in the twelfth century. 
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <strong><a src="https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Prose_Edda">Prose Edda</a></strong> - A collection of tales and the Norse creation myth as compiled by Snorri Sturluson sometime in the thirteenth century, possibly as early as 1220.
